Praca domowa temat -Liniar equations-

zadanie 1

  1. \(-31-4x = -5-5(1+5x)\)

  2. \(8x+4(4x-3) = 4(6x+4) - 4\)

  3. \(4(-8x+5) = -32x-26\)

zadanie 2

  1. \(5(x-3) - 7(6-x) = 24-3(8-x)-3\)

  2. \(8(x-1) + 17(x-3) = 4(4x-9) +4\)

  3. \(15(x-1) + 4(x+3) = 2(7+x)\)

zadanie 3

  1. \(\frac{4x}{5} - \frac{7}{4} = \frac{x}{5} + \frac{x}{4}\)

  2. \(5x-6(x-5) = 2(x+5)+5(x-4)\)

  3. \((x+15)(x-3) - (x^2-6x+9) = 30-15(x-1)\)

zadanie 4

  1. \(\frac{x-2}{2}+\frac{x+10}{9} = 5\)

  2. \(\frac{x+35}{6} - \frac{x+7}{9} = \frac{x+21}{4}\)

  3. \((x+1)(2x+1) = (x+3)(2x+3)-14\)

zadanie 5

  1. \(5x - [(4x-7)(3x-5)] = 6-3[(4x-9)(x-1)]\)
